meanings.definition: Not suitable for printing or publication.
meanings.sent1: The document contained unprintable content that was too sensitive to share.
meanings.sent2: The blurry photo was unprintable and needed to be retaken.
meanings.sent3: The joke was so unprintable that it left everyone in stitches.
meanings.sent4: Her emotions were like an unprintable novel, too complex to be captured on paper.
meanings.sent5: The graffiti on the wall was so unprintable that it had to be painted over immediately.

meanings.definition: Unable to be printed or reproduced.
meanings.sent1: The corrupted file was unprintable and could not be opened.
meanings.sent2: The faded text on the old manuscript was unprintable due to its poor condition.
meanings.sent3: The secret code was intentionally made unprintable to protect classified information.
meanings.sent4: His memories were like unprintable photographs, fading with time and impossible to replicate.
meanings.sent5: The ancient scroll was so fragile and unprintable that it had to be preserved in a special case.
